-- Hyundai Motor Plans $451 Million JV Vehicle Plant in Sichuan, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-21T17:55:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/hyundai-motor-plans-451-million-jv-vehicle-plant-in-sichuan-xinhua-says.html
Hyundai Motor Co. signed an
agreement with Sichuan Nanjun Automotive Group to build a 3
billion yuan ($451 million) joint-venture auto plant, Xinhua
News Agency said, withouth citing anyone.  The plant in Ziyun city in the southwestern province of
Sichuan will produce commercial and electric- and gas-powered
vehicles, Xinhua said. The plant will have an annual capacity of
200,000 units by 2013 and 700,000 by 2020, Xinhua said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  